node.text:
IT'S THE NPS-AVERSARY!
From the early days of "hey, maybe we should keep this place wild", through pivotal moments of the very fabric of modern American history, the NPS continues to protect and preserve the places that make us who we are. 
Today marks 103 years of National Parks Service – we think a toast is in order! Video by @maxeyfish #radparks #findyourpark

node.title: The (unofficial) History of the National Parks

node.accessibility_caption: Three national park scented candles in 6oz tins on a wooden desk with a potted fern sitting behind them.

node.text: Fill your home with the smell of Honeysuckle, Sagebrush, and freshly chopped Fraser fir—floral scents found in our national parks that transport you to the jagged peaks of Grand Teton, foggy mountain tops of the Great Smoky Mountain, and the wild grasslands of Yellowstone. Which scent is your favorite? #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter

node.accessibility_caption: An evening shot of the Morning Glory pool in Yellowstone National Park.

node.text:
Originally named for its incredible likeness to the flower, the Morning Glory pool in @Yellowstonenps has changed color over the past century due to vandalism and the declining pool temperatures. While the colors are still remarkable, it is important to always practice Leave No Trace principles when visiting parks we love. Have you visited this iconic pool yet? #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

Photo by @audacityofamber
📍Photo taken on Crow, Eastern Shoshone, and Cheyenne native lands.

Notice: While we continue to share photos and stories from the wild lands we love, keep in mind, every park has different opening dates and restrictions. Be sure you are following all local, state, and federal guidelines.

node.text: Happy 105th birthday @hawaiivolcanoesnps and @haleakalanps! 🎉 Looking for a birthday gift that shows your love for these island parks and gives back with every purchase? Grab our Wide Wale Cord hat and support the Hawaii Pacific Parks Association in style! #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter

node.text:
@grandtetonnps is a favorite among park lovers, and it's no secret why. With rugged mountain peaks, blankets of wildflowers, and 310,000 acres to explore, peak visitation in 2021 is to be expected. Wanna know an insider tip? #planlikearanger by arriving early to beat the crowds, and be sure you have reservations if you're staying overnight! What's your favorite spot in the park? 

Photo by @davidmrule
📍Photo taken on Shoshone-Bannock, Eastern Shoshone, and Cheyenne native lands. #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter

node.text: Going for a hike this weekend? Be sure to #planlikearanger and pack plenty of water! Stay hydrated all summer long and give back to parks you love with our Peaceful Bear Water Bottle. #radparks #leaveitbetter #findyourpark

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Parks Project in Lake Clark National Park & Preserve with @parksproject, @erinoutdoors, and @lakeclarknps. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
It's the weekend, treat yourself! 🐻 Bears are commonly seen around this time of year in many of our national parks, and @Lakeclarknps is no exception. When visiting bear country, remember to:

🐾 Hike in groups of 4 or more for greater safety.
🔊 Make noise! Call out or clap regularly to make your presence known.
🥪 Store your food properly! Never leave food, garbage, kitchenware, etc. unattended.
🔎 Be aware of your surroundings

Photo by @erinoutdoors
📍Photo taken on Dena'ina, Yup'ik, and Sugpiaq native lands. #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

node.text: 2022 is around the corner and if you're like us, you're already planning upcoming trips for next year! Our National Parks 2022 Wall Calendar features unique graphics of some of our favorite parks, and might spark some inspiration for your next adventure 😉  Where are you headed next? #findyourpark #radparks #leaveitbetter

node.text:
It's #wildflowerwednesday and we absolutely love these lupines blooming in Mount Rainier right now 💜 August is peak wildflower season, and on your visit, you'll encounter all sorts of species native to the region, like Avalanche lilies, asters, daisies, fireweed, and purple shooting stars! What's your favorite wildflower?

Remember to practice Leave No Trace principles and do not damage or harvest wildflowers. #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

Photo by @michaeljlindquist

node.text:
Want an up close view of one of the country's most iconic waterfalls? Yosemite Falls Trail is one of @yosemitenpss oldest historic trails, leading to the top of North America’s tallest waterfall. Along the way, you'll have a birds-eye view of the valley below and stunning views of Half Dome 🏞️ Be sure to wear appropriate hiking gear and practice Leave No Trace during your visit! #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter
